<subSubSection id="0B2E0C88BDCD2CBAC8CA012B58B7D735" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="7" pageNumber="56" type="type">
<paragraph id="6DE2E0BFC4358B91F78AEF7D47E5FEF5" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="78EDA7D0D956F4F5C084E4246DFFD900" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicName id="C42B6BE79DF083AF02042E0E27EBB38B" authorityName="Robinson &amp; Keeley &amp; Skvarla &amp; Chan" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Robinson &amp; Keeley &amp; Skvarla &amp; Chan" baseAuthorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachycalyx">
<emphasis id="57E4AC67B1FDCAC557FB3F82AE97B74A" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Vernonia brachycalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
O. Hoffm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE402F7436289D02D1BDAF703BBEC4F7" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">
Scrambling shrubs; stems slender with solid pith, somewhat deflected at nodes in upper part of vegetative plant and in inflorescence; hairs of stems L-shaped, with long, multicellular, uniseriate stalk and elongate, horizontal cap cell mounted near one end. Leaves alternate, petioles slender and 7-15 mm long below basal acumination of blade; blades ovate, 6-7 times longer than petiole, 5-10 cm long, 1.5-5.0 cm wide, base broadly obtuse to short-acute, narrowly acuminate at petiole, margins remotely denticulate to nearly entire, apex scarcely to gradually acuminate, surfaces pilosulous and 
<pageBreakToken id="F75B989167A597FBD596BC3B9094652B" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" start="start">with</pageBreakToken>
glandular dots, hairs sparser above, dense on larger veins; secondary veins pinnate, with ca. 6 weak secondary veins on each side of midrib, spreading at ca. 40-45° angles. Inflorescences broadly corymbiform, with branches elongate, mostly with small or insignificant bracteoles at bases; peduncles 2-30 mm long. Heads campanulate; involucre much shorter than florets at maturity; involucral bracts in 2-3 series, persistent, oblong-lanceolate, with acute to short-acuminate tips, puberulous outside, pale at base, midvein broadly greenish, percurrent at tip, lateral margins thinly membranous; receptacle scarcely convex, epaleate, epilose. Florets ca. 15 in a head, homogamous, bisexual; corollas violet to purple, narrowly funnelform, with long basal tube, throat short, lobes narrowly oblong-lanceolate, with glandular dots outside; anthers with triangular apical appendages; base of style slightly enlarged, style shaft glabrous, sweeping hairs on style branches elongate with rounded or blunt tips. Achenes 5-angled, with some glandular dots and short setulae, surface with sparse idioblasts and inner layer with small subquadrate or rounded raphids; pappus pale to sordid or rufous, 2 series, inner pappus of many capillary bristles that are slightly broader in distal half, outer pappus of short narrow scales. Pollen grains 40 
<normalizedToken id="0C1A344F14B1D559F4ECD0046EB3607C" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in diam., Type A, sublophate. 2n = 20 (
<bibRefCitation id="C1000A2A74F66156EF9AF5AD036AF6CE" author="Jones, SB" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="14" pageNumber="63" pagination="126 - 127" refId="B12" refString="Jones, SB, 1982. IOPB Chromosome Numbers Reports LXXIV. Taxon 31: 126 - 127" title="IOPB Chromosome Numbers Reports LXXIV." volume="31" year="1982">Jones 1982</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="1110CE3A68EFAB2F1E3183DB028B74C2" authorityName="Robinson &amp; Keeley &amp; Skvarla &amp; Chan" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Robinson &amp; Keeley &amp; Skvarla &amp; Chan" baseAuthorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachycalyx">
<emphasis id="9C97661306A0C345E0B08E15A4513597" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="57">Vernonia brachycalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4136F822A3FB1DB9E172DC403F105611" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D936286C30D6AD1080F34650969AF0FB" pageId="8" pageNumber="57">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4E6B1B7AAD2B267C8B6C71A95696169B" pageId="8" pageNumber="57">
The name 
<taxonomicName id="7FDEE331B7136CC45EA7AB9082A21D4B" authorityName="H. Rob., S. C. Keeley &amp; Skvarla" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hoffmannanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1892F77214D1F5954CEC70007AAC7C78" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="57">Hoffmannanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered appropriate, since both of the older species names featured here were published by 
<bibRefCitation id="D79D04F353AABBD1A24D57DE6AE60C48" author="Hoffmann, O" journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie" pageId="14" pageNumber="63" pagination="219 - 237" refId="B7" refString="Hoffmann, O, 1894. Compositae africanae. II. Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 20: 219 - 237" title="Compositae africanae. II." volume="20" year="1894">Hoffmann (1894</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="81597ABB89B9DEB791EDC57B13F34CA6" author="Hoffmann, O" journalOrPublisher="Die Pflanzenwelt Ost-Afrikas und der Nachbargebiete" pageId="14" pageNumber="63" pagination="402 - 422" refId="B8" refString="Hoffmann, O, 1895. Compositae. Die Pflanzenwelt Ost-Afrikas und der Nachbargebiete vol. C: 402 - 422" title="Compositae." volume="vol. C" year="1895">1895</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
